## input
10 # length of warehose (vertical length)
69 42 68 76 40 87 14 65 76 81 # L numbers
50 # height adjust numbers

## question
After m height adjustments, print out the difference between the heighest and the lowest
Height adjustment means moving one box from the heighest to the lowest

import sys
sys.stdin=open("input.txt","rt")

length=int(input())
num=list(map(int, input().split()))
tot=int(input())

for i in range(tot):
    num.sort()
    num[0]+=1
    num[length-1]-=1

num.sort()
print(num[length-1]-num[0])
